    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-cuban-style-chicken-and-pepper-stew/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based <strong>hob-safe</strong> <strong>oven-proof casserole dish </strong>with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-cuban-style-chicken-and-pepper-stew/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced</strong> <strong>beefe </strong>to the dish with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook for 2-3 min or until starting to brown</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-cuban-style-chicken-and-pepper-stew/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and chop your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s] </strong>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop into rough chunks</p><p>Crush your <strong>garlic </strong>open by squashing it with the side of a knife and remove the skins</p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>kidney beans</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-cuban-style-chicken-and-pepper-stew/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Reduce the heat to medium</p><p>Add the <strong>onion wedges</strong> and <strong>chopped pepper</strong> to the dish with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong>, the <strong>crushed garlic</strong>, <strong>black beans</strong>, <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>bay leaf[ves] </strong>and <strong>ground cumin</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Add 500ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[750ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [1L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>,<strong> </strong>your <strong>beef stock mix</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong> and <strong>red wine paste</strong> and stir it all together</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-cuban-style-chicken-and-pepper-stew/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cover with the lid and put the dish in the oven for 1 hour or until the sauce is rich and the beef is tender \u2013 this is your<strong> Cuban-style beef & pepper stew</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-cuban-style-chicken-and-pepper-stew/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the stew has been cooking for 45 min, add your <strong>white long grain rice </strong>and <strong>cauliflower rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 110ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[175ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [225ml]</span> cold water and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-cuban-style-chicken-and-pepper-stew/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> Cuban-style beef & pepper stew</strong> over the <strong>cooked cauliflower rice</strong> and tear your <strong>coriander</strong> over the top</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
